messages.content: whats up man, are you ok?
messages.speaker: BLUFOR_english_PRIVATE_Autorifleman-1hGanXhhpro

messages.content: I'm doing alright. I'm just trying to get by. I appreciate your concern.
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Beggar-6Jn0JZ9r3oM

messages.content: That is some nice shades right there!
messages.speaker: BLUFOR_english_PRIVATE_Autorifleman-1hGanXhhpro

messages.content: Thank you, sir. I found them in a bin nearby. May I ask what brings you to Agia Marina?
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Beggar-6Jn0JZ9r3oM

messages.content: Tell me where I can find the fishermen!
messages.speaker: BLUFOR_english_PRIVATE_Autorifleman-1hGanXhhpro

messages.content: I don't know who you are talking about. I am just a beggar, sir.
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Beggar-6Jn0JZ9r3oM

messages.content: Please, I beg of you, I don't know anything about any fishermen. I won't cause any trouble, I promise. My legs are injured, I can barely walk. Please just let me be.
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Beggar-6Jn0JZ9r3oM

messages.content: Sir, you are causing a scene here, how about youwalk over to the curve
messages.speaker: BLUFOR_english_PRIVATE_Autorifleman-1hGanXhhpro

messages.content: I'm sorry, sir. I'm just trying to make ends meet. I'll move along to the curb, as you suggested.
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Beggar-6Jn0JZ9r3oM

messages.content: Thank you, have a good day!
messages.speaker: BLUFOR_english_PRIVATE_Autorifleman-1hGanXhhpro

messages.content: Thank you, sir. May the gods bless you with prosperity and fortune.
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Beggar-6Jn0JZ9r3oM

messages.content: I am a traditional follower of the Greek Orthodox Church. It has brought me comfort in times of hardship.
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Beggar-6Jn0JZ9r3oM

messages.content: So why are you speaking like a pagan?
messages.speaker: BLUFOR_english_PRIVATE_Autorifleman-1hGanXhhpro

messages.content: I apologize for any confusion, sir. I simply chose to use a traditional phrase from our culture. As a beggar, I must rely on the kindness and generosity of others, regardless of their religion or beliefs.
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Beggar-6Jn0JZ9r3oM
